We Koreans are celebrating the moment talking about a famous quote said by the first government leader of Republic of Korea, Kim Goo.
"I do not want any power to conquer the world, what I only want is the power of culture, which can truly make my people flourish." He lived during the darkest period of human history(Imperialism and WW2), and was murdered by the S.Korean dictator as he tried to prevent Korea from dividing into two. 75 years have passed since then and we Koreans are now appreciating his wonderful words.
